Description: Fragment of flattened handle of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp with grape cluster symbol. Clay near fine pink-red.
Curator's comments: Name Mousaios. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.200, 38. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0391.01.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1191)
